In [8]:
#Fill up the empty age values with mean of the same sex, pclass, and embark data.
age_nan = []
for i in range(len(data['PassengerId'])):
    if str(data['Age'][i]) == 'nan':
        age_nan.append([data['PassengerId'][i],data['Pclass'][i],data['Sex'][i],data['Embarked'][i]])
    else: pass

for j in age_nan:
    same = 0
    num = 0
    for k in range(891):
        if data['Pclass'][k] == j[1] and data['Sex'][k] == j[2] and data['Embarked'][k] == j[3] and str(data['Age'][k]) != 'nan':
            same = data['Age'][k] + same
            num = num + 1
        else: pass
    mean = same / num
    data['Age'][j[0]-1] = round(mean,0)

data6 = data5.drop(['PassengerId','Name','Famsit','Ticket'], axis=1)

test2 = test1.drop(['PassengerId','Name','Parch','Ticket'], axis=1)
data6['Embarked'] = data6['Embarked'].map( {'S': 0, 'C': 1, 'Q': 2} ).astype(int)
data6['Sex'] = data6['Sex'].map( {'male': 0, 'female': 1} ).astype(int)

test2 = test2.rename(columns={'SibSp':'Family'})
